INSERT INTO pullreq VALUES('pullreq','"Z2l0aHViLmNvbTowMTA6UmVwb3NpdG9yeTMyNjY5NzcyNDpwdWxscmVxODE="','"Z2l0aHViLmNvbTowMTA6UmVwb3NpdG9yeTMyNjY5NzcyNA=="',81,'merged','"RePierre"','"Unified reading of image for both color and grayscale mode"','"2022-07-03T20:03:08Z"','"2022-07-03T20:05:27Z"','"2022-07-03T20:04:32Z"','"2022-07-03T20:04:31Z"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'"main"','"deloro-project/rocc-pipelines"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'"Regardless of how the image is read (color or grayscale), after reading the image a check is performed to see whether the data from the image is None. If data is None, then the function will return False; otherwise it will continue with the export. Closes #79."','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound',NULL);
INSERT INTO pullreq VALUES('pullreq','"Z2l0aHViLmNvbTowMTA6UmVwb3NpdG9yeTMyNjY5NzcyNDpwdWxscmVxODI="','"Z2l0aHViLmNvbTowMTA6UmVwb3NpdG9yeTMyNjY5NzcyNA=="',82,'merged','"RePierre"','"Migrated export of Yolo v5 annotations from Github Actions to cron"','"2022-07-03T21:35:57Z"','"2022-07-04T11:06:28Z"','"2022-07-03T21:38:33Z"','"2022-07-03T21:38:33Z"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'"main"','"deloro-project/rocc-pipelines"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'"This pull request contains the following changes:\n- A new file containing image resolutions to export was added\n  This file will be read by the `cron` job that executes the export, and it will run the export for each of the resolutions specified in this file.\n- The Python script for exporting Yolo v5 annotations was changed to support two verbs - ''characters'', and ''letters''\n  Using verbs when running the Python script will trigger only the specified type of export which will reduce the time it takes for the export. Subsequently, the export shell script was changed to only export character annotations at this time.\n- A new parameter was added to the Python export script called `blur-workers`\n  As a workaround for issue #77, this parameter will allow to execute the blur sequentially on the machines where blurring in parallel fails.\n- The `Export Yolo v5 Annotations` action was replaced with `Make shell scripts executable`\n  Since we are interested in running the export in `cron` it doesn''t make sense to keep the export action. The new action is intended to make the export script executable such that it can be called by `cron`.\n\nCloses #80."','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound','eieio-unbound',NULL);
